# üêû bug report


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
css code:
```css
:host-context(.aaa .bbb) {
  .my-class { color: red; }
}
```

Build into rule without spaces:
```
.aaa.bbb[_nghost-%COMP%] .my-class[_ngcontent-%COMP%],
.aaa.bbb [_nghost-%COMP%] .my-class[_ngcontent-%COMP%]{ color: red }
```

I think host context should save own css selector without modification.
In serve mode it works correctly.


